The paper proposes a novel neural network model for automatic question generation, which is a problem in natural language processing. The model uses a bidirectional LSTM architecture with a copying mechanism component to generate more suitable questions adaptively from input data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
